emuInput.TitMainTitle: Bride Amanda Bussey Henderson wearing satin gown with lace train, long lace sleeves, and lace yoke with satin edge, holding bouquet of lilies, posed in home of Mr. and Mrs. James Bussey, Singer Place
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1951, pg. 10 reads: " Mrs. Jesse T. Henderson - Harris Photo." Portion of accompanying article reads: "Mary Amanda Bussey, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. James Bussey of Singer Place, was married on Sept. 1 at Trinity AME Church to Jesse T. Hendersosn [Henderson] Jr., son of Mr. and Mrs. Jesse T. Henderson, Amsterdam, N.Y."
